msgctxt "56_Whiny Man"
msgid "Forget it! Those girls hate my guts!"
msgstr "¡Olvidalo! ¡Esas mujeres me odian!"

msgctxt "68_Calming Woman"
msgid "Don't give up now... After all, you've only seen three of\\r\n"\n"them."
msgstr "No te rindas, además... Solo has visitado a tres mujeres."

msgctxt "80_Whiny Man"
msgid "Yeah, and each one gave me the same open-mouthed stare. My\\r\n"\n"best jokes flew right over their heads!"
msgstr "Sí, y todas me miraron raro. ¡Mis chistes son de lo peor!"

msgctxt "92_Whiny Man"
msgid "I'm tellin' you, it isn't workin' out! It's no use. I'll\\r\n"\n"never manage an article on hostess club tips and tricks."
msgstr "¡Ya te lo dije! Esto no está funcionando. Nunca podré escribir\\r\n"\n"una revista sobre consejos y trucos para charlar con anfitrionas."

msgctxt "104_Akiyama"
msgid "Excuse me. I hate to interrupt, but if you're not going in,\\r\n"\n"would you mind moving aside?"
msgstr "Perdonen, odio interrumpir, pero... Les importaría\\r\n"\n"dejarme pasar, ¿por favor?"

msgctxt "128_Calming Woman"
msgid "Ah, sorry! We'll get out of your way."
msgstr "Ah, ¡lo siento mucho! Ya nos vamos."

msgctxt "140_Akiyama"
msgid "Wait, aren't you Minamizawa-san? From the Mars Fighters\\r\n"\n"comedy duo? Wow! I'm a big fan of yours!"
msgstr "Un momento, porfavor. ¿Usted no es Minamizawa-san del dúo de\\r\n"\n"comediantes Mars Fighters? ¡Soy admirador suyo!"

msgctxt "152_Calming Woman"
msgid "See, Minamizawa-san? I told you you had plenty of fans in\\r\n"\n"Kanto."
msgstr "¿Lo ves, Minamizawa-san? Te dije que en Tokio\\r\n"\n"tenías admiradores."

msgctxt "164_Akiyama"
msgid "Are you here for work? Hope it goes well. I'll be rooting\\r\n"\n"for you."
msgstr "¿Está aquí por trabajo? Espero que le vaya bien.\\r\n"\n"Si necesita algo, cuente conmigo."

msgctxt "176_Minamizawa"
msgid "Thanks a lot. I appreciate it!"
msgstr "¡Muchas gracias! Lo aprecio mucho."

msgctxt "188_Calming Woman"
msgid "(Minamizawa-san, this is your chance! This fan of yours seems to know the nightlife around here. Maybe he can tell us about the hostess clubs.)"
msgstr "(Minamizawa-san, ¡esta es tu oportunidad! Este admirador tuyo parece\\r\n"\n"vivir aquí. Tal vez pueda contarnos sobre los clubes de anfitrionas.)"

msgctxt "200_Minamizawa"
msgid "(What are you talkin' about? You want me to embarrass myself in front of a fan!?)"
msgstr "(¿De qué estás hablando? ¡¿Quieres que me avergüence enfrente de un fan?!)"

msgctxt "212_Calming Woman"
msgid "(Here's the thing, Minamizawa-san. Entertainers have to be responsible if they want to get hired back. Fulfilling your assignment is paramount.)"
msgstr "(Mira, Minamizawa-san. Los famosos deben ser responsables si quieren ser\\r\n"\n"contratados o no. Cumplir con tu trabajo es importante.)"

msgctxt "224_Calming Woman"
msgid "(Keep up the spoiled-brat act, and I'll see to it you never darken the doorstep of our publishing house again.)"
msgstr "(Si vas a seguir quejándote me aseguraré de que nunca te representemos otra vez.)"

msgctxt "236_Minamizawa"
msgid "All right. Okay. I'll do it."
msgstr "(¡Está bien! De acuerdo, hagámoslo.)"

msgctxt "248_Calming Woman"
msgid "Excuse me! Do you happen to frequent hostess clubs, if I may\\r\n"\n"be so bold as to ask?"
msgstr "Disculpe, ¿siempre va a clubes de anfitrionas?"

msgctxt "260_Akiyama"
msgid "Hm? Yeah, I guess you could say that."
msgstr "Hmm, sí, podría decirse que sí."

msgctxt "272_Ashibe"
msgid "Wonderful! Allow me to introduce myself. I am Ashibe, an\\r\n"\n"editor for \"Casanova,\" a magazine for men who want to\\r\n"\n"become more popular with the ladies. And, er..."
msgstr "¡Genial! Permíteme presentarme. Soy Ashibe, editora de “Casanova”, una revista para\\r\n"\n"hombres que quieren hacerse más populares con las mujeres. ¿Y usted es...?"

msgctxt "284_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, I'm Akiyama."
msgstr "Oh, mucho gusto, soy Akiyama."

msgctxt "296_Ashibe"
msgid "The thing is, Akiyama-san, we've commissioned a series of\\r\n"\n"articles from Minamizawa-san here on some tips to use at the\\r\n"\n"clubs Jewel and Shine."
msgstr "Akiyama-san, lo que pasa es que le pedimos a Minamizawa-san escribir\\r\n"\n"consejos para usar en los clubes Jewel y Shine."

msgctxt "308_Ashibe"
msgid "But it seems they do things differently out west, where\\r\n"\n"Minamizawa-san is from. He's having a hard time hitting it off with these Tokyo girls."
msgstr "Pero parece que en el oeste, donde vive Minamizawa-san, las cosas se hacen\\r\n"\n"de diferente modo. Y está teniendo dificultades para conectar con las chicas de Tokio."

msgctxt "320_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, I'm sorry to hear that..."
msgstr "Oh, ya veo..."

msgctxt "332_Ashibe"
msgid "Do you think you could give Minamizawa-san a little info on\\r\n"\n"some of the girls at the clubs I've mentioned?"
msgstr "¿Cree que podría ayudar a Minamizawa-san sobre cómo platicar co\\r\n"\n"las chicas de los clubes que le mencioné?"

msgctxt "344_Ashibe"
msgid "I'll pay you for your time, of course. Come on,\\r\n"\n"Minamizawa-san. Don't you have something to add?"
msgstr "Le compensaré por su tiempo, claro. Bien, Minamizawa-san, ¿algo qué decir?"

msgctxt "356_Minamizawa"
msgid "Please...?"
msgstr "¿Por favor?..."

msgctxt "368_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, I guess I could tell you about a couple of my\\r\n"\n"favorites..."
msgstr "Bueno, creo que la mayoría de mis consejos podrían servirle..."

msgctxt "380_Ashibe"
msgid "That would be wonderful! Thank you very much!"
msgstr "¡Eso es genial! ¡Muchas gracias!"

msgctxt "392_Ashibe"
msgid "We're working out of Cuez Bar in the Kamurocho Underground\\r\n"\n"Mall. Could you stop by there when you have some info for\\r\n"\n"us?"
msgstr "Trabajamos en Cuez Bar en el centro comercial subterráneo de Kamurocho.\\r\n"\n"¿Podría pasarse por allí una vez tenga información para nosotros?"

msgctxt "404_Minamizawa"
msgid "Please, whenever you can!"
msgstr "¡Por favor, tómese su tiempo!"

msgctxt "416_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure thing. I'll see you later, then."
msgstr "Claro, nos vemos luego entonces."

